habitat_description: In Arkansas, Plethodon kiamichi is found under rotting logs, stumps, and rocky debris within rocky, and moist wooded slopes (Trauth et al. 2004). They are commonly found at higher elevations in the Round and Kiamichi Mountains of western Arkansas and southeastern Oklahoma (Black and Seivert 1989, Highton et al. 1989, Anthony 2005).
